cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB 

The paper discusses the security and privacy concerns of centralized online social networks and proposes a decentralized approach with policies for membership and interaction. This aligns with the topics covered in the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.DB (Databases). However, since the paper focuses more on security and privacy, cs.CR is the most likely category, followed by cs.SI and cs.DC.
